Implement the public `sequence/2` function.

`sequence(name, formatter_fn)` returns the next value for the named sequence.
It should first make sure the backing Agent is running by calling
`ensure_agent_started/0`. Then it must atomically fetch-and-increment the counter
for `name` using `Agent.get_and_update/2` on `@agent`: look up the current count
for `name` in the state map (defaulting to `0` when the sequence has never been
used), add `1` to get the next integer `n`, store the updated count back under
`name`, and have the update return `n`. Finally, call `formatter_fn.(n)` and
return its result. Each distinct `name` keeps its own independent counter that
starts at `1`, and the atomic update keeps sequences safe for concurrent
(`async: true`) tests. The function head should guard that `formatter_fn` is a
one-arity function.

